7 An Act relating to emergency medical services;
amending 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-2502, which relates
8 to legislative findings and declarations; declaring
emergency medical services to be considered essential
9 services for certain purpose; and declaring an
emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-2502, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 1-2502. The Legislature hereby finds and declares that:
16 1. There is a critical shortage of providers of emergency care
17 for:
18 a. the delivery of fast, efficient emergency medical care
19 for the sick and injured at the scene of a medical
20 emergency and during transport to a health care
21 facility, and
22 b. the delivery of stabilizing and definitive care at a
23 health care facility; and
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 206 Page 1

1 2. Improved emergency service is required to reduce the
2 mortality rate during the first critical minutes immediately
3 following the onset of a medical emergency; and
4 3. Solely for purposes of eligibility for federal funding,
5 emergency medical services provided by an ambulance service managed
6 by a municipality, county, ambulance service district, tribal
7 entity, or other public entity shall be considered essential
8 services.
9 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
13 Passed the Senate the 4th day of March, 2026.
